
			
									<h5>Release Date: 20 April 2022</h5>
				
									Neo4j 4.3.12 is a maintenance release with many important improvements and fixes.
<h3>Highlights</h3>

<ul>
   <li>Update jackson-databind from 2.12.6 to 2.13.2.2 (and thus also com.fasterxml.jackson.* from 2.12.6 to 2.13.2), to address CVE-2020-36518</li>
   <li>neo4j-admin import respects dbms.logs.debug.format setting</li>
   <li>Fix bug where you could get an error message like Cannot put key x before first key y, for example in queries using SelectOrSemiApply or ConditionalApply and Limit.</li>
   <li>Usages of GetDegree wasnâ€™t obvious in the plan description. Now instead

of size([pattern]) usages of GetDegree will be rendered with getDegree([pattern])</li>
   <li>Before this change, pattern expressions in boolean contexts were marked as deprecated. This deprecation was removed.</li>


</ul>
  

<h3>Detailed Changes and Docs</h3>
For the complete list of all changes, please see <a href="https://github.com/neo4j/neo4j/wiki/Neo4j-4.3-changelog" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">the changelog</a>.
Look for 4.3 Operations manual <a href="https://neo4j.com/docs/operations-manual/4.3/">here</a>.				
					